OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FTurkish journalists        
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdetained over quake        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Freporting                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Freelance journalist Mir Ali Kocer was 
OL,6, 200 miles from the epicentre when      
OL,7, Turkey was struck by a deadly          
OL,8, earthquake on 6 February. Grabbing his 
OL,9, camera and microphone, he drove down to
OL,10, the affected region to interview       
OL,11, survivors.                             
OL,13,FHe shared stories of survivors and     
OL,14,Frescuers on Twitter and is now under   
OL,15,Finvestigation on suspicion of spreading
OL,16,F"fake news" and could face up to three 
OL,17,Fyears in jail.                         
OL,19,FHe is one of at least four journalists 
OL,20,Fbeing investigated for reporting or    
OL,21,Fcommenting on the earthquake.          
